    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>By tweaking the precise modulation of your music’s output frequency, you can now use it to distract or debilitate your enemies. As a standard action, you can target a single creature within 15 feet and unleash a rush of highly compressed discordant music at them. The target must attempt a @Check[type:fortitude]{Fortitude save} (DC = 10 + half your character level + your key ability modifier)[[10 + @details.level.value + @data.attributes.keyability]]. If the target succeeds, they’re @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.D8JvCEmOiWKe2UDx]{deafened} for 2 rounds. On a failure, the target is @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.D8JvCEmOiWKe2UDx]{deafened} and @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.yUtkoIshf4dPruNd]{off-target} for a number of rounds equal to the insight bonus of your first music genre. If the target fails this save by 10 or more, they’re also @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.LoRydw1D4bqlbkA2]{nauseated} for 1 round.</p>"
    },
